testcase.name: When we have a user with 51d172788b034b738565f7dd4d4cb2fe as id, and user with c4e935b546d04f73829a955281b88292 as id and want to set maximum amount to transfer at 0.01 when we validate we expecting that result is: true

When we have a user with 51d172788b034b738565f7dd4d4cb2fer as id, and user with c4e935b546d04f73829a955281b88292 as id and want to set maximum amount to transfer at 0.01 when we validate we expecting that result is: false

When we have a user with 51d172788b034b738565f7dd4d4cb2fe as id, and user with c4e935b546d04f73829a955281b8829 as id and want to set maximum amount to transfer at 0.01 when we validate we expecting that result is: false

When we have a user with 51d172788b034b738565f7dd4d4cb2fe as id, and user with null as id and want to set maximum amount to transfer at 0.01 when we validate we expecting that result is: false

When we have a user with 51d172788b034b738565f7dd4d4cb2fe as id, and user with <script>alert('hello josdem')</script> as id and want to set maximum amount to transfer at 0.01 when we validate we expecting that result is: false
